 of critical cultural awareness within foreign language/culture education, and to inspire a proposal for teacher education and development. Finally, this book submits a general proposal for the development of critical cultural awareness and intercultural communication competence among prospective and practising teachers of foreign languages/cultures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCritical pedagogy. 0aLanguages, ModernxStudy and teaching. 0aLangues vivantesxÉtude et enseignement. 0aMulticultural education. 0aPédagogie critique. 0aÉducation interculturelle. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh1 aSilva, Duarte M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978185359611740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781853596117423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781853596117/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK